<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1320187 size-full" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/695-03381104en_Masterfile.jpg?resize=450%2C318&#038;ssl=1" alt="Your DUSTBIN as goldmine for fraudsters ― DCP Tunji" width="450" height="318" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/695-03381104en_Masterfile.jpg?w=450&amp;ssl=1 450w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/695-03381104en_Masterfile.jpg?resize=300%2C212&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/695-03381104en_Masterfile.jpg?resize=58%2C41&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/695-03381104en_Masterfile.jpg?resize=260%2C184&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/695-03381104en_Masterfile.jpg?resize=184%2C130&amp;ssl=1 184w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Deputy Commissioner of Police and Commander of Rapid Response Squad in Lagos State, DCP Tunji Disu, has advised Nigerians to always guard their information jealously and stop dumping vital documents that contain personal information in the dustbin. He urged Nigerians to shred their bank statements, utility bills, old signed Cheques, Documents, used boarding passes after use. According to the DCP who made this disclosure on twitter,  bin raiders search the bins, steal vital information and use them for fraud. “Your DUSTBIN as a goldmine for fraudsters. Average dustbins contain, bank statements, utility bills, old signed Cheques, Document with full names, addresses, phone nos, dates of birth, bank Accts, sort codes. Bin raiders search ur bins, steal your vital info for fraud. Guard your info jealously” Your DUSTBIN as goldmine for fraudsters.Average dustbins contain,bank statements,utility bills,old signed Cheques,Document with full names,addresses,phone nos,dates of birth,bank Accts,sort codes.Bin raiders search ur bins,steal your vital info for fraud.Guard your info jealously — DCP Tunji Disu (@TunjiDisu1) December 7, 2019  Vanguard News Nigeria Mr Emmanuel Chile, the General Manager of Benue State Environmental Sanitation Authority (BENSESA), said the agency inaugurated ‘operation show your dustbin’ to curb the indiscriminate dumping of refuse in Makurdi. August 11, 2018 In "News" The monster of e-fraud long predicted in advanced economies is now here with us in Nigeria in full swing. The dominant force is driven by young people between 20 and 30 years. Here is the report. May 6, 2019 In "Business" With current attempts by fraudsters to access people’s bank accounts through text messages, emails, phone calls etc., it is important we are armed with the knowledge of the different ways our bank accounts can be hacked by these fraudsters. February 9, 2017 In "News"